      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "High-density zoning is a vital strategy for urban revitalization because it maximizes land efficiency, reduces traffic congestion, and fosters vibrant, walkable communities that encourage social interaction. By concentrating housing and commercial spaces, cities can lower infrastructure costs per resident while creating diverse neighborhoods that support local businesses and reduce reliance on automobiles. This approach directly tackles housing affordability crises by allowing for more units on less land, ensuring that major metropolitan areas remain economically dynamic and socially inclusive for all residents.",
